summary: I am a motivated geologist currently working at Deltares. I have a lot of passion for the (Dutch) subsurface and its role in the energy transition. In addition to my work and related activities, I like to travel, sing and I practice various (outdoor) sports. I would describe myself as enthusiastic, honest and communicative, critical and analytical.

projects: [{'title': 'WarmingUP: "Formation, lithology and region-specific stress field in the Netherlands - Implications for fault stability in geothermal doublets"', 'date': {'start': {'month': 10, 'day': None, 'year': 2021}, 'end': {'month': 10, 'day': None, 'year': 2021}}, 'description': 'Within the national project WarmingUP, I worked on the in-situ, tectonic stress field in the subsurface of the Netherlands, specific for different tectonic regions, lithologies and stratigraphic formations. Emphasis was put on the implications of this for fault stability and induced seismicity in geothermal target formations in the Netherlands. This project was part of my internship at TNO.', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Eva', 'last_name': 'Bakx', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Advisor/Researcher Applied Geology at Deltares'}]}, {'title': 'Master thesis: "The interaction between long-term wedge growth and the occurrence of earthquakes in subduction zones: insights from analogue modelling"', 'date': {'start': {'month': 12, 'day': None, 'year': 2020}, 'end': {'month': 10, 'day': None, 'year': 2021}}, 'description': "I presented my MSc thesis at the NAC 2021 (Dutch Earth Scientific Congress) during an oral presentation. The subject of my MSc thesis was the interaction between long-term wedge growth and the occurrence of earthquakes in subduction zones. Analogue modelling was used as a method to get new insights in the interaction between the short-term (seismicity) and long-term (permanent wedge growth) deformation processes. This project was done in the Earth Simulation Laboratory and was a collaboration between the Teclab and the HPT-lab. Image data was acquired using a high speed camera (high spatial and temporal resolution) producing so-called 'big data'. Mechanical data was produced by a loadcell and displacement sensor. The data were processed using Matlab and Python. The skills I achieved during this project allow me to obtain and process data with different types of apparatus and software and to find practical solutions to experimental challenges. \nThe thesis was supervised by dr. Ernst Willingshofer and dr. André Niemeijer. Grade: 8.", 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Eva', 'last_name': 'Bakx', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Advisor/Researcher Applied Geology at Deltares'}]}, {'title': 'Symposium - Polar Extremes: From Science to Policy', 'date': {'start': {'month': 9, 'day': None, 'year': 2020}, 'end': {'month': 1, 'day': None, 'year': 2021}}, 'description': "I was part of the organization of the Earth Science symposium 'Polar Extremes: From Science to Policy', which found place on the 12th of January 2021. In this symposium, 6 lecturers enlightened the path from science to policy concerning climate change in the polar regions. This included the development of climate policy in ministries, the various Earth Science related subjects that are necessary to make policy and future projections of the climate in the polar regions.", 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Eva', 'last_name': 'Bakx', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Advisor/Researcher Applied Geology at Deltares'}]}, {'title': 'Bachelor thesis: "Kinematics of deformation on the North-eastern part of Skiathos island, Greece"', 'date': {'start': {'month': 4, 'day': None, 'year': 2018}, 'end': {'month': 7, 'day': None, 'year': 2018}}, 'description': "BSc Thesis: 'Kinematics of deformation on the North-eastern part of Skiathos island, Greece', supervised by Dr. Ernst Willingshofer and Prof. Dr. Dimitrios Sokoutis.
